ordered-list.list-item:
Edit the configuration file for the nginx reverse proxy, which is located in the directory /etc/nginx/conf.d. Redirect traffic away from the Sync Gateway node or nodes that you will upgrade during this iteration, distributing the traffic over the remaining nodes. Following are before and after examples of the upstream directive in the configuration file. In this example, we will upgrade node 41 first. Node 44 is the spare node, which is already running the new version of Sync Gateway.
Before:
upstream sync_gateway {
    server 172.20.30.41:4984;
    server 172.20.30.42:4984;
    server 172.20.30.43:4984;
}
After:
upstream sync_gateway {
    server 172.20.30.41:4984 down;
    server 172.20.30.42:4984;
    server 172.20.30.43:4984;
    server 172.20.30.44:4984;
}
The distribution of traffic will remain one-third of the traffic on each of three nodes (41, 42, and 43 before this reload and 42, 43, and 44 afterwards).

Edit the configuration file for the nginx reverse proxy, which is located in the directory /etc/nginx/conf.d.
If you are retiring a different spare node (43), the edit would be:
Before:
upstream sync_gateway {
    server 172.20.30.41:4984;
    server 172.20.30.42:4984 down;
    server 172.20.30.43:4984;
    server 172.20.30.44:4984;
}
After:
upstream sync_gateway {
    server 172.20.30.41:4984;
    server 172.20.30.42:4984;
    server 172.20.30.43:4984 down;
    server 172.20.30.44:4984;
}
If you are retiring the original spare node (44), the edit would be:
Before:
upstream sync_gateway {
    server 172.20.30.41:4984;
    server 172.20.30.42:4984;
    server 172.20.30.43:4984 down;
    server 172.20.30.44:4984;
}
After:
upstream sync_gateway {
    server 172.20.30.41:4984;
    server 172.20.30.42:4984;
    server 172.20.30.43:4984;
    server 172.20.30.44:4984 down;
}
